 Merquior's favourite themes – liberalism as it relates to social cohesion, political stability, morality, republicanism and democracy, and the relativeness and scepticism that characterize postmodern thinking. The book's application to two regions of the world – to Merquior's own Latin America and to Central and Eastern Europe – is direct and obvious.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  a20th century.  aBrazil.  aConservatism.  aEthics.  aFestschrift.  aPolitical theory.  aTrust.1 aAlarcon, Victor, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBobbio, Norberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoudon, Raymond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCampos, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCansino, Cesar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCansino, Cesar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGellner, Ernest, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGellner, Ernest, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHall, John A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIonescu, Ghita, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaguaribe, Helio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Gregory R, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLafer, Celso, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMaiz, Ramon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMerquior, Jose G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruytert